Professional Life Insurance Options.usecases: Providing life insurance coverage for Federal employees and retirees, offering Basic life insurance coverage and three Optional insurance options
Professional Life Insurance Options.solutions: The Federal Employees' Group Life Insurance (FEGLI) Program provides group term life insurance, covering over 4 million Federal employees and retirees, as well as their family members. It consists of Basic life insurance coverage and three options, with the cost of Basic insurance shared between the individual and the Government.

key_features.Basic life insurance coverage: Automatically covered for most new Federal employees, with premiums deducted from paycheck unless waived
key_features.Optional insurance options: Consist of three forms of Optional insurance that individuals can elect, with enrollment not automatic and requiring action to elect the options
key_features.Cost sharing: The cost of Basic insurance is shared between the individual and the Government, while the individual pays the full cost of Optional insurance
